SIMPLE: pallial
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pallial
<hw>Pal"li*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pallium</ets> a mantle. See <er>Pall</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a mantle, especially to the
mantle of mollusks; produced by the mantle; <as>as, the <ex>pallial</ex>
line, or impression, which marks the attachment of the mantle on the
inner surface of a bivalve shell</as>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Bivalve</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pallial chamber</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
cavity inclosed by the mantle.</cd> -- <col><b>Pallial sinus</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>an inward bending of the pallial line, near the
posterior end of certain bivalve shells, to receive the siphon. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Bivalve</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palliament</ent>⟦br⟧
